reviews.review_text: Had a steady Job..... F*** YEAH this is why the GRATEFUL DEAD RULE THE KNOWN UNIVERSE..Playin opener > Crazy fingers..then a SICK SICK WEST LA and a KILLER LOSER !!! DID I SAY PLAYIN OPENER IN NYC ????

Niiiice I just had to comment on this show.  OK, there's afew things to note.  1.)  Opening with Playin'!
2.)  The Crazy Fingers is friggin' insane.  One of the better I've heard recently.  Be prepared...
3.) West LA Fadeaway has some funky lyrics towards the end, makes you kind of sit up and listen  "what's he gonna say next"
that's as far as i'm into it, I'm going right back in and listening to Crazy Fingers again.  My God man!
9-21-82 Awesome show, set list and recording. Thanks C Miller.

Solid show I've started to really like the later half of '82. This is a good show but a notch below some of the other high points of fall 82. The Playin>Crazy Fingers opener is great (check out 09/15 for an ever better version) and High Time is always a nice touch. Other than that, this is a solid show and a good listen but nothing that'll blow you away.

Reaching for a gold ring down inside... Nice sound to this one..NYC brought out the best in the in the band and it shows in this solid show..Love the High Time..so please> GIVE IT A WHIRL!!!!!! Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!
Big River Schredded to Smithereens. Hope Johnny C spun this one before he checked out.

This show is a classic example of why 80s Dead is so fascinating. You just never know what you might hear, or in what order.
This was my go to version until the box set dropped. Credit to Charlie Miller, I don't really hear much of a difference.
